"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-fourth-turning-is-here-and-end-times-3439006b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">末日：精英、反精英和政治瓦解之路</a></h3><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-fourth-turning-is-here-and-end-times-3439006b"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823326?width=639&amp;height=971" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">企鹅出版社</span></div></div></div><p><strong>作者：彼得·图尔钦</strong><em>企鹅出版社</em></p><p>精英阶层的生产过剩加剧了美国不断扩大的贫富差距——对一些人来说，这种结合只能预示着国家即将崩溃。多米尼克·格林评论。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-fourth-turning-is-here-and-end-times-3439006b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阅读评论</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-who-organized-nature-review-linnaeus-the-namer-673a3305?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">组织自然的人：林奈的一生</a></h3><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-who-organized-nature-review-linnaeus-the-namer-673a3305"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823329?width=639&amp;height=965" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">普林斯顿大学</span></div></div></div><p><strong>作者：冈纳·布罗伯格</strong>|<em>普林斯顿大学</em></p><p>瑞典博物学家林奈对自然世界进行了有序的分类，但他对动植物的热爱却是古怪而个人化的。克里斯托夫·伊姆舍尔评论。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-man-who-organized-nature-review-linnaeus-the-namer-673a3305?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阅读评论</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><h3> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-peoples-justice-review-the-originalist-and-the-masses-d683b2fa?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人民正义：克拉伦斯·托马斯和定义他的宪法故事</a></h3><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-interactiveLink"><div class="image-container"> <a class="interactive-link" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-peoples-justice-review-the-originalist-and-the-masses-d683b2fa"><img width="16" height="10" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-823330?width=639&amp;height=964" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><span class="image-interactive-icon">
            </span></a></div><div class="wsj-article-caption"><span class="wsj-article-credit">监管网关</span></div></div></div><p><strong>作者：阿穆尔·塔帕尔</strong>|<em>监管网关</em></p><p>一位联邦法官认为，当我们遵循最高法院法官托马斯的论点来适用宪法时，弱者和无权者将受益最大。大卫·J·加罗评论。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-peoples-justice-review-the-originalist-and-the-masses-d683b2fa?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阅读评论</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
